rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Something that is performed by an agent and has a well-defined beginning time and ending time. This is the broadest classification of the events done by an agent, and it includes business acquisitions, communication and other social actions, using devices, and commercial actions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an action to a piece of software that is able to execute the action.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Action Handler

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an action to the performer of the action.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Action Performer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an action to an Internet API that is capable of executing the action.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Internet API

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an action to an object of the action, i.e. the patient or the result of the action. The patient is present when the action begins, and the result is brought into being by the action.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Action Object

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an action to the person for whom the action is performed, the beneficiary of the action.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Action Recipient

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration type containing standard descriptors for the completion of an action, e.g. 'attempted', which means that the action was done but was not necessarily successful, 'made', which means that the action was done and was successful, and 'missed', which means that the action was done and was not successful.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Action Completion

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration value representing the concept of 'attempted' actions, actions that were done, whether successfully or not.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Attempted

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration value representing the concept of actions that were successful.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Made

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration value representing the concept of actions that were not successful.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Made

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration representing the concept of percentages, which are the percentages of made actions against attempts. In sports contexts, this is the success rate.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Percentage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Anything that can act autonomously and thus perform actions. This type covers people.person, organization.organization, and business.operation. Note that this type should be used in cases of "legal personhood", where an organization, location or other entity is regarded as having certain rights/responsibilities.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Agent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links an agent to an action performed by the agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:event.agent to the mso:location.address. This is the address associated with the mso:event.agent. This can be a residential or commercial address, a mailing address or any other physical address associated with the entity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Address

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an agent to an address line of the agent's address. This is used only for conflation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Address Line

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an agent to the postal code of the agent's address. This is used only for conflation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Postal Code

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an agent to an organization to which the given agent is connected, e.g. as a member, a current/former student, a current/former employee, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Affiliation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an agent to information about the various ways in which the agent may be contacted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Contact Information

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an mso:event.agent to the mso:finance.expense_relationship that collects data about the agent's types of expenses. Expenses are the different outflows of money and types of expenses are the categories of costs for a given entity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Expenses

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:event.agent to the mso:finance.income_tax_filing_form the agent must file.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Filing Requirement

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:event.agent to information about its financial performance.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Financial Performance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property that indicates that the second agent has had an effect on the character, development or behavior of the first agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Influenced by

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates that the first agent has had an effect on the character, development or behavior of the second agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Influences

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:event.agent to the things for which the agent is known.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Known For

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:event.agent to the mso:law.legal_cases in which the agent has been involved.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legal Cases

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:event.agent to an mso:location.location associated with the mso:event.agent. This can be either a residential or commercial location associated with the entity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an agent to information about the structures that the agent occupied and during what time frames.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Occupancy

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an agent to the agent's official webpage. Note that the virtual property definition here needs to be modified by adding the following statement to the "where" clause: ?agent mso:type.object.type mso:event.agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Official Webpage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:event.agent to the mso:common.operator_relationship that expresses data about a thing the agent operates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating an agent to an ownership relationship in which the agent is an owner of some asset.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Owner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates two agents when each influences the other.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Peers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an agent to an event, in the sense of a large gathering of people, where the agent performs, e.g. as a speaker or singer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Performance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:event.agent to the mso:government.political_position_relationship containing data on given political views.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Political View

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an agent to information about the previous names held by an agent (and when those names were valid).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Previous Names

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an agent to information about the membership of elements of the agent in social networks. For example, this property would be used to specify the number of members of an organization who are also members of a given social network or the number of people who hold a given job title who are members of a given social network.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social Network Membership

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an agent to information about the number of profiles that the agent has on a social network.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social Network Use

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a agent to an identity that the person, group, organization or company has on a social networking site.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social Network User
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: This property is too restrictive, since there are many social network profiles that do not correspond to agents, e.g. those for video games, movies, and books. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:ratings.rated_entity.social_network_user]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an agent to information about a sponsor (financial or otherwise).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sponsor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an agent to another agent that is an element of the first. This property is most useful for agents that are not subtyped as organizations, groups or people, but are made up of other agents. For example, the Wright Brothers can be considered a single agent that is made up of Orville Wright and Wilbur Wright.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subagent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:event.agent to the mso:law.crime_type of which the agent was a victim.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Victim of Crime Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:event.agent to the instances of video content featuring, or in some other way related to, the agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Video Content

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data on all assassination events. Note this collection does not include unsuccessful attempts at an assassination, which are covered by mso:event.assassination_attempt.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Assassination

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:event.assassination to the mso:event.agent responsible for the assassination.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Assassinated By

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:event.assassination to the mso:people.person that was the victim of assassination. This property is currently broad and may include both intended and unintended victims of an assassination.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Assassination Victim

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data on all attempted assassination events. Note this collection does not include successful attempts at an assassination, which are covered by mso:event.assassination. Currently, this relationship does not include event.action, as it is not necessarily clear if an attempted assassination has a well-defined beginning and ending time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Attempted Assassination

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:event.assassination_attempt to the mso:event.agent responsible for the attempted assassination.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Attempted By

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:event.assassination_attempt to the mso:people.person that was the intended target of assassination.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Assassination Target

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A significant event, e.g. a famous speech.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Big Moment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a big moment to an audio recording of the big moment.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Audio Recording
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use event.speech_or_presentation.track instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:event.speech_or_presentation.track]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Big moment ID
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Big moment ID
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use type.object.key instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:type.object.key]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Video recording of big moment
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Video recording
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: A similar property can be added to event.speech_or_presentation if needed. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all actions in which a user blocks another. Blocking can prevent the blocked user from responding or even seeing any content from the user.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Block Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Any action that is performed with the physical body, e.g. eating, digestion, touching, walking, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bodily Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An action that involves receiving the right to use an object for a limited period of time, e.g. borrowing a book from a library.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Borrow Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Giving money to an agent in exchange for ownership of a product or service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Buy Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an action of buying to an event ticket that is purchased.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Event Ticket

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an action of buying to a theater showtime for which the buyer has purchased a ticket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Film Showing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a buy action to the payment method, e.g. cash or credit card, that was used in the purchase.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Payment Method

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a buy action to the price, per unit, of what was purchased.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Price

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a buy action to the number of units of the product purchased.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quantity Purchased

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a buy action to the agent that sells the product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Seller

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a action of buying to a transit pass that is purchased.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Transit Pass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all check ins. These are the actions in which a user adds code or other contributions in a working copy into the repository.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Checkin

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all choosing actions. These are the events in which an agent selects an option or object from a set.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Choose Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A computer action that involves closing a file on a device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Close File Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an action of closing a file to the file that is closed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: File

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all actions in which an agent comments on an item on a webpage: a blog post, an article, a review, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Comment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An action that involves a monetary transaction or the intent to complete a monetary transaction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commercial Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An action that involves flying as a passenger on a commercial airline. Note that this covers both flights consisting of several legs, as well as flights involving a single airplane, a single departure location, and a single arrival location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commercial Flight Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a flight to the airline (or one of the airlines) with which the flight is associated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airline

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight action to the airport where the flight ends.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Arrival Airport

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight action to the gate of the airport where the flight arrives.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Arrival Gate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight action to the time that the flight is scheduled to end.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Arrival Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight to the action of buying a ticket for the flight.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Buy Ticket

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight to an action of checking in for the flight.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Checkin

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight to an action of checking the status of the flight, viz. whether/when it departed and when it is due to arrive.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Confirm Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight action to the date that the ticket was issued to the passenger.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Ticket Issued

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight to the airport where the flight begins.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Departure Airport

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight to the gate of the airport where the flight departs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Departure Gate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight to the time that the flight is scheduled to begin.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Departure Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight to the identifier for the flight, e.g. US Air 321.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flight Identifier

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a flight to another flight that is part of it. This property can be used to link connecting flights together.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flight Leg

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight to an action of booking a seat on the flight.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Make Reservation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight to the number of stops that the flight makes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Stops

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a commercial flight action to the number of the ticket held by the passenger.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ticket Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all communication actions. These are events in which an agent intends to communicate with another agent, and includes verbal and non-verbal communications. A bee may communicate the existence of a food source to the hive by dancing, a person may nod to another in affirmation, and an organization may communicate with members by a newsletter.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Communicate Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An action that involves considering two or more objects and noting their similarities and differences.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Comparison Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An action that can be performed only with a computer or similar device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer action to the computer that is used to complete the action.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An action that involves interacting with a piece of content, whether static, e.g. a textual document or an image, or dynamic, e.g. a video or audio file.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Content Consumption Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Altering a piece of content in some way, viz. creating, deleting or updating it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Content Modification Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all creation events. This is an event in which an agent creates a new thing that previously did not exist. Creation may use previously existing materials, for example, using concrete, lumber, and drywall to create a house, or the creation action may be purely conceptual, for example creating a new theory or hypothesis.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Create Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all deceptions. These are the misleading falsehoods perpetuated by an agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Deception

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all disasters. Disasters are the events that create ruin or misfortune on an area or for a set of people. They may have natural causes, such as earthquakes or tornados, or may be man-made, for example disasters caused by terrorism or industrial accidents.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Disaster

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a disaster to the locations that are/were directly affected by the disaster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Areas Affected

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:event.disaster to its cause, if any is determined.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cause

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a disaster to the official monetary estimate of the damage wrought by the disaster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Damage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a disaster to a person who survived the disaster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Survivor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a disaster to a standard descriptor to classify the type of disaster, e.g. tropical cyclone, shooting or explosion.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Type of Disaster

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a disaster to a person who was directly affected by the disaster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Victim

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a disaster to a number indicating how many people died as a direct result of the disaster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fatalities

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a disaster to a number indicating how many people were seriously hurt (requiring hospitalization, whether it was available or not under the circumstances) but not killed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Injuries

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a disaster to a famous person who was killed as a direct result of the disaster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Notable People Killed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a disaster to a prominent structure that was damaged as a direct result of the disaster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Notable Structures Damaged

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:event.disaster to the number of survivors of the disaster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Survivors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:event.disaster to the number of people left homeless by it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Left Homeless

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a disaster to a structure that was damaged as a direct result of the disaster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Structures Damaged

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a disaster to a structure that was rendered uninhabitable as a direct result of the disaster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Structures Destroyed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a disaster to a structure in the affected area that was still inhabitable after the disaster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Surviving Structures
Disaster-affected structure
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: There is no need to reify this concept as a type. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:architecture.structure]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: destroyed_by_disaster
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. If needed, a comparable property can be added to architecture.structure. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: survived_disasters
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. If needed, a comparable property can be added to architecture.structure. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all attributed causes of disasters. A disaster may be caused by human intent or error, as in terrorism or industrial accidents, or may caused by natural factors, for example an earthquake or tornado.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Disaster Cause
Disaster survivor
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: There is no reason to reify this concept as a type. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: survived_disasters
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. If needed, a comparable virtual property can be added to event.agent. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains standard descriptors to classify kinds of disasters, e.g. tropical cyclone, shooting or explosion.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Disaster Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a standard descriptor for a kind of disaster to an example of this kind of disaster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Disasters of this Type
Disaster victim
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: There is no reason to reify this concept as a type. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: killed_in_disaster
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. If needed, a comparable virtual property can be added to event.agent. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An action that involves granting ownership of an object to someone else without the expectation of receiving anything in return, e.g. giving money to a charity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Donate Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A computer action that involves transferring a file from a server to a client.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Download Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a download action to the client to which the file is downloaded.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Download Client

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a download action to the file that is downloaded.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Downloaded File

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a download action to the server from which the file is downloaded.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Download Server

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The bodily action of ingesting a beverage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Drinking

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing instances of shaking of the earth that are caused by a sudden release of energy from the lithosphere.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Earthquake

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an earthquake to the depth in kilometers of the earthquake.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Depth

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an earthquake to an entity representing a standard descriptor for the kind of earthquake.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Earthquake Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an earthquake to the point on the earth's surface directly above the point where the earthquake originates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Epicenter
